==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Chirm
<hw>Chirm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS. <ets>cirm</ets>,
<ets>cyrm</ets>.]</ety> <def>Noise; din; esp.; confused noise, clamor,
or hum of many voices, notes of birds, or the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chirm</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Chirm
<hw>Chirm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Cf. AS.
<ets>cyrman</ets>, <ets>cirman</ets>, to cry out. ⟦root⟧24. Cf.
<er>Chirp</er>.]</ety> <def>To chirp or to make a mournful cry, as a
bird.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Huloet.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chirognomy</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Chirm
<hw>Chirm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>
}</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Chirm</er>.]</ety> <def>Clamor, or
confused noise; buzzing.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>churme</qex> of a thousand taunts and reproaches.</q>
<rj><qau>Bacon.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Churn</ent>⟦br⟧
